# SSH Routes Configuration
# Format: NETWORK/CIDR via JUMP_CHAIN
# Jump chains are comma-separated: user@host1,user@host2,user@host3

# ==========================================
# Cyber Polygon Network Topology
# ==========================================

# Primary Kali jump host
# All networks go through kali first
# kali.cyberpolygon.com -> 203.0.113.10

# ==========================================
# Internal Networks (through specific VMs)
# ==========================================

# Network 1: 192.168.1.0/24
# Accessible via: Kali -> VM1 (192.168.1.10)
# VM1 has secondary adapter on this network
192.168.1.0/24 via root@kali,admin@192.168.1.10

# Network 2: 192.168.2.0/24
# Accessible via: Kali -> VM2 (192.168.2.10)
# VM2 has secondary adapter on this network
192.168.2.0/24 via root@kali,admin@192.168.2.10

# Network 3: 10.0.5.0/24
# Accessible via: Kali -> VM3 (10.0.5.1)
# VM3 has secondary adapter on this network
10.0.5.0/24 via root@kali,user@10.0.5.1

# Network 4: 172.16.0.0/16
# Large network accessible via: Kali -> VM4 -> Internal Gateway
# Multi-hop for deep network access
172.16.0.0/16 via root@kali,admin@172.16.1.1,root@172.16.1.254

# ==========================================
# DMZ Networks
# ==========================================

# DMZ Network: 10.10.0.0/16
# Accessible via: Kali -> DMZ Gateway
10.10.0.0/16 via root@kali,admin@10.10.0.1

# ==========================================
# Management Networks
# ==========================================

# Management Network: 192.168.100.0/24
# Direct access through Kali only
192.168.100.0/24 via root@kali

# ==========================================
# Default Route
# ==========================================

# For any network not explicitly defined above
# Try through primary Kali jump host
default via root@kali

# ==========================================
# Direct Access (no jump host)
# ==========================================

# If you have direct access to certain networks
# from your workstation (uncomment and configure)
# 192.168.50.0/24 via direct

# ==========================================
# Notes
# ==========================================
# - Replace hostnames/IPs with your actual infrastructure
# - Replace usernames (root, admin, user) with actual users
# - More specific routes are matched first
# - Default route is used if no match found
# - Use "direct" for networks accessible without jump host
# - Test routes with: ./ssh-router.sh -r ssh-routes.conf -l
